Movie.create!([
  {title: "Star Wars: Episode IV - A New Hope", description: "The Imperial Forces -- under orders from cruel Darth Vader (David Prowse) -- hold Princess Leia (Carrie Fisher) hostage, in their efforts to quell the rebellion against the Galactic Empire. Luke Skywalker (Mark Hamill) and Han Solo (Harrison Ford), captain of the Millennium Falcon, work together with the companionable droid duo R2-D2 (Kenny Baker) and C-3PO (Anthony Daniels) to rescue the beautiful princess, help the Rebel Alliance, and restore freedom and justice to the Galaxy.", movie_length: "2:01", director: "George Lucas", rating: "PG", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzVlY2MwMjktM2E4OS00Y2Y3LWE3ZjctYzhkZGM3YzA1ZWM2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkwMjQ5NzM@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "Iron Man", description: "A billionaire industrialist and genius inventor, Tony Stark (Robert Downey Jr.), is conducting weapons tests overseas, but terrorists kidnap him to force him to build a devastating weapon. Instead, he builds an armored suit and upends his captors. Returning to America, Stark refines the suit and uses it to combat crime and terrorism", movie_length: "2:06", director: "Jon Favreau", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://i.etsystatic.com/10791463/r/il/a11b08/1321062493/il_fullxfull.1321062493_izrb.jpg"},
  {title: "The Boondock Saints", description: "Tired of the crime overrunning the streets of Boston, Irish Catholic twin brothers Conner (Sean Patrick Flanery) and Murphy (Norman Reedus) are inspired by their faith to cleanse their hometown of evil with their own brand of zealous vigilante justice. As they hunt down and kill one notorious gangster after another, they become controversial folk heroes in the community. But Paul Smecker (Willem Dafoe), an eccentric FBI agent, is fast closing in on their blood-soaked trail.", movie_length: "1:50", director: "Troy Duffy", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "data:image/jpeg;base64,"},
  {title: "Venom: Let There Be Carnage", description: "Eddie Brock is still struggling to coexist with the shape-shifting extraterrestrial Venom. When deranged serial killer Cletus Kasady also becomes host to an alien symbiote, Brock and Venom must put aside their differences to stop his reign of terror.", movie_length: "1:37", director: "Andy Serkis", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a7/Venom_Let_There_Be_Carnage_poster.jpg"},
  {title: "The Shawshank Redemption", description: "Andy Dufresne (Tim Robbins) is sentenced to two consecutive life terms in prison for the murders of his wife and her lover and is sentenced to a tough prison. However, only Andy knows he didn't commit the crimes. While there, he forms a friendship with Red (Morgan Freeman), experiences brutality of prison life, adapts, helps the warden, etc., all in 19 years.", movie_length: "2:22", director: " Frank Darabont", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://www.filmsite.org/posters/shawshankredemption.jpg"},
  {title: " The Godfather", description: "Widely regarded as one of the greatest films of all time, this mob drama, based on Mario Puzo's novel of the same name, focuses on the powerful Italian-American crime family of Don Vito Corleone (Marlon Brando). When the don's youngest son, Michael (Al Pacino), reluctantly joins the Mafia, he becomes involved in the inevitable cycle of violence and betrayal. Although Michael tries to maintain a normal relationship with his wife, Kay (Diane Keaton), he is drawn deeper into the family business.", movie_length: "2:55", director: "Francis Ford Coppola", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2MyNjYxNmUtYTAwNi00MTYxLWJmNWYtYzZlODY3ZTk3OTFlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkwMjQ5NzM@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "The Hurt Locker", description: "Following the death of their well-respected Staff Sergeant in Iraq, Sergeant JT Stanborn and Specialist Owen Eldridge find their Explosive Ordnance Disposal unit saddled with a very different team leader. Staff Sergeant William James is an inveterate risk-taker who seems to thrive on war, but there's no denying his gift for defusing bombs.", movie_length: "2:11", director: "Kathryn Bigelow", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/91AJTg-4SiL._RI_.jpg"},
  {title: "The Truman Show", description: "He doesn't know it, but everything in Truman Burbank's (Jim Carrey) life is part of a massive TV set. Executive producer Christof (Ed Harris) orchestrates \"The Truman Show,\" a live broadcast of Truman's every move captured by hidden cameras. Cristof tries to control Truman's mind, even removing his true love, Sylvia (Natascha McElhone), from the show and replacing her with Meryl (Laura Linney). As Truman gradually discovers the truth, however, he must decide whether to act on it.", movie_length: "1:43", director: "Peter Weir", rating: "PG", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91QkSivUP9L._SL1500_.jpg"},
  {title: "Finding Nemo", description: "Marlin (Albert Brooks), a clown fish, is overly cautious with his son, Nemo (Alexander Gould), who has a foreshortened fin. When Nemo swims too close to the surface to prove himself, he is caught by a diver, and horrified Marlin must set out to find him. A blue reef fish named Dory (Ellen DeGeneres) -- who has a really short memory -- joins Marlin and complicates the encounters with sharks, jellyfish, and a host of ocean dangers. Meanwhile, Nemo plots his escape from a dentist's fish tank.", movie_length: "1:40", director: "Andrew Stanton", rating: "G", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/p_findingnemo_19752_05271d3f.jpeg?region=0%2C0%2C540%2C810"},
  {title: "Stagecoach - 1939", description: "John Ford's landmark Western revolves around an assorted group of colorful passengers aboard the Overland stagecoach bound for Lordsburg, New Mexico, in the 1880s. An alcoholic philosophizer (Thomas Mitchell), a lady of ill repute (Claire Trevor) and a timid liquor salesman (Donald Meek) are among the motley crew of travelers who must contend with an escaped outlaw, the Ringo Kid (John Wayne), and the ever-present threat of an Apache attack as they make their way across the Wild West.", movie_length: "1:36", director: "John Ford", rating: "Not Rated ", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://www.filmsite.org/posters/stagecoach.jpg"},
  {title: "India Sweets and Spices", description: "After returning from college, young Alia upends her family's well-ordered life with her brash new independence. When secrets about her parents come to light during a dinner party, it soon pushes her to a daring and ultimately hilarious confrontation.", movie_length: "1:41", director: "Geeta Malik", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNGVjMWVjYTEtZWE5Zi00NzMwLWIxZmUtMThhMzhmNmQ5NjU3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjUwNTg1Ng@@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "#Alive", description: "While a grisly virus ravages a Korean city, Joon-woo tries to stay safe by locking himself inside his apartment. Just as he loses hope, he discovers another survivor.", movie_length: "1:39", director: "Il Cho", rating: "Not Rated ", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://d2ajy4iry6zk4j.cloudfront.net/pubvat/thumbnail/large/pkd4hb55u"},
  {title: "Blackfish", description: "Tilikum, a captive killer whale, has taken the lives of three people. This impassioned documentary tells his story to unravel the consequences of keeping orcas in captivity and reveal how little is known about these highly intelligent mammals.", movie_length: "1:30", director: "Gabriela Cowperthwaite", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "data:image/jpeg;base64,"},
  {title: "Notes on a Scandal", description: "Barbara Covett (Judi Dench), a veteran teacher at St. George's, senses a kindred spirit in Sheba Hart (Cate Blanchett), the school's new art teacher. The younger woman's charisma intensely draws in the older, and the two become friends. Then Barbara learns of Sheba's affair with a teenage student and becomes the keeper of the explosive secret.", movie_length: "1:38", director: "Richard Eyre", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTgyOWQ4ZTUtMmQ0ZS00M2MxLThhMTctODBjMGVmNzMwYTFhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzQyMDgzOTU@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "Office Space", description: "Corporate drone Peter Gibbons (Ron Livingston) hates his soul-killing job at software company Initech. While undergoing hypnotherapy, Peter is left in a blissful state when his therapist dies in the middle of their session. He refuses to work overtime, plays games at his desk and unintentionally charms two consultants into putting him on the management fast-track. When Peter's friends learn they're about to be downsized, they hatch a revenge plot against the company inspired by \"Superman III.\"", movie_length: "1:29", director: "Mike Judge", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://encrypted-tbn2.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ3t60xIVT3NIbT6DY9NXgue3AjhA0gHy85fPSMCqwsACBhm-q-"},
  {title: "Charlie's Angels", description: "Elena Houghlin is a scientist, engineer and inventor of Calisto -- a sustainable energy source that will revolutionize the way people use power. But when the cutting edge technology falls into the wrong hands, Elena turns to the Townsend Agency for help. Now, it's up to the Angels -- Jane, Sabina and the newly recruited Elena -- to retrieve Calisto before it can be transformed into a weapon of mass destruction.", movie_length: "1:58", director: "Elizabeth Banks", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/charlies_angels_2019.jpg"},
  {title: "One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest", description: "When Randle Patrick McMurphy (Jack Nicholson) gets transferred for evaluation from a prison farm to a mental institution, he assumes it will be a less restrictive environment. But the martinet Nurse Ratched (Louise Fletcher) runs the psychiatric ward with an iron fist, keeping her patients cowed through abuse, medication and sessions of electroconvulsive therapy. The battle of wills between the rebellious McMurphy and the inflexible Ratched soon affects all the ward's patients.", movie_length: "2:13", director: "Miloš Forman", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/2/26/One_Flew_Over_the_Cuckoo%27s_Nest_poster.jpg"},
  {title: "Monsters, Inc.", description: "Monsters Incorporated is the largest scare factory in the monster world, and James P. Sullivan (John Goodman) is one of its top scarers. Sullivan is a huge, intimidating monster with blue fur, large purple spots and horns. His scare assistant, best friend and roommate is Mike Wazowski (Billy Crystal), a green, opinionated, feisty little one-eyed monster. Visiting from the human world is Boo (Mary Gibbs), a tiny girl who goes where no human has ever gone before.", movie_length: "1:36", director: "Pete Docter", rating: "G", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://lumiere-a.akamaihd.net/v1/images/p_monstersinc_19751_55afa07a.jpeg"},
  {title: "The Devil Wears Prada", description: "Andy (Anne Hathaway) is a recent college graduate with big dreams. Upon landing a job at prestigious Runway magazine, she finds herself the assistant to diabolical editor Miranda Priestly (Meryl Streep). Andy questions her ability to survive her grim tour as Miranda's whipping girl without getting scorched.", movie_length: "1:46", director: "David Frankel", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjQ3ZTIzOTItMGNjNC00MWRmLWJlMGEtMjJmMDM5ZDIzZGM3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTkzODUwNzk@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "AVP: Alien vs. Predator", description: "When the wealthy and ambitious Charles Bishop Weyland (Lance Henriksen) funds an expedition to Antarctica, he hopes to find a mysterious source of heat that has been detected. Led by a tough guide, Alexa Woods (Sanaa Lathan), Weyland and his team uncover a pyramid, but they also find malevolent parasitic aliens. Making matters worse, another extraterrestrial species, known as Predators, arrive to hunt the other aliens, with the humans caught in the middle of the conflict.", movie_length: "1:55", director: "Paul W. S. Anderson", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f7/Avpmovie.jpg"},
  {title: "Groundhog Day", description: "A cynical TV weatherman finds himself reliving the same day over and over again when he goes on location to the small town of Punxsutawney to film a report about their annual Groundhog Day. His predicament drives him to distraction, until he sees a way of turning the situation to his advantage.", movie_length: "1:41", director: "Harold Ramis", rating: "PG", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWIxNzM5YzQtY2FmMS00Yjc3LWI1ZjUtNGVjMjMzZTIxZTIxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjU0OTQ0OTY@._V1_FMjpg_UX1000_.jpg"},
  {title: "Meet the Fockers", description: "Now that Greg Focker is \"in\" with his soon-to-be in-laws, Jack and Dina Byrnes, it looks like smooth sailing for him and his fiancée, Pam. But that's before Pam's parents meet Greg's parents, the Fockers. The hyper-relaxed Fockers and the tightly-wound Byrneses are woefully mismatched from the start, and no matter how hard Greg and Pam try, there is just no bringing their families together. This all adds up to a disastrously funny time of getting to know you.", movie_length: "1h 55m", director: "Jay Roach", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWZjODQxMWMtZmIzYS00YjMwLWFiZTctYmFiZmJiNjljYWVmL2ltYWdlL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTQxNzMzNDI@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "Ocean's Eleven", description: "Dapper Danny Ocean (George Clooney) is a man of action. Less than 24 hours into his parole from a New Jersey penitentiary, the wry, charismatic thief is already rolling out his next plan. Following three rules: Don't hurt anybody, don't steal from anyone who doesn't deserve it, and play the game like you've got nothing to lose. Danny orchestrates the most sophisticated, elaborate casino heist in history.", movie_length: "1:56", director: "Steven Soderbergh", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzVmYzVkMmUtOGRhMi00MTNmLThlMmUtZTljYjlkMjNkMjJkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDk3NzU2MTQ@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "Ocean's Twelve", description: "After successfully robbing five casinos in one night, Danny Ocean (George Clooney) and his crew of thieves have big problems. Despite pulling off one of the biggest heists in Las Vegas history, the members of the gang have already spent much of the money they stole. Casino owner Terry Benedict (Andy Garcia) demands that Ocean return the money, plus millions more in interest. Unable to come up the cash, the crew is forced to come together to pull off another series of heists, this time in Europe.", movie_length: "2:5", director: "Steven Soderbergh", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://i0.wp.com/www.seenit.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/oceans_12.jpg?resize=1600%2C2133"},
  {title: "The Fifth Element", description: "In the 23rd century, a New York City cabbie, Korben Dallas (Bruce Willis), finds the fate of the world in his hands when Leeloo (Milla Jovovich) falls into his cab. As the embodiment of the fifth element, Leeloo needs to combine with the other four to keep the approaching Great Evil from destroying the world. Together with Father Vito Cornelius (Ian Holm) and zany broadcaster Ruby Rhod (Chris Tucker), Dallas must race against time and the wicked industrialist Zorg (Gary Oldman) to save humanity.", movie_length: "2:6", director: "Luc Besson", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/71ME0xLcEDL._AC_SL1006_.jpg"},
  {title: "Pirates of the Caribbean: The Curse of the Black Pearl", description: "Capt. Jack Sparrow (Johnny Depp) arrives at Port Royal in the Caribbean without a ship or crew. His timing is inopportune, however, because later that evening the town is besieged by a pirate ship. The pirates kidnap the governor's daughter, Elizabeth (Keira Knightley), who's in possession of a valuable coin that is linked to a curse that has transformed the pirates into the undead. A gallant blacksmith (Orlando Bloom) in love with Elizabeth allies with Sparrow in pursuit of the pirates.", movie_length: "2:23", director: "Gore Verbinski", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/8/89/Pirates_of_the_Caribbean_-_The_Curse_of_the_Black_Pearl.png"},
  {title: "Jurassic Park", description: "In Steven Spielberg's massive blockbuster, paleontologists Alan Grant (Sam Neill) and Ellie Sattler (Laura Dern) and mathematician Ian Malcolm (Jeff Goldblum) are among a select group chosen to tour an island theme park populated by dinosaurs created from prehistoric DNA. While the park's mastermind, billionaire John Hammond (Richard Attenborough), assures everyone that the facility is safe, they find out otherwise when various ferocious predators break free and go on the hunt", movie_length: "2 hours 7 mins", director: "Steven Spielberg", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/e7/Jurassic_Park_poster.jpg"},
  {title: "Catwoman - 2004", description: "\"Catwoman\" is the story of shy, sensitive artist Patience Philips (Halle Berry), a woman who can't seem to stop apologizing for her own existence. She works as a graphic designer for Hedare Beauty, a mammoth cosmetics company on the verge of releasing a revolutionary anti-aging product. When Patience inadvertently happens upon a dark secret her employer is hiding, she finds herself in the middle of a corporate conspiracy. What happens next changes Patience forever.", movie_length: "1:44", director: "Pitof", rating: "PG-13", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/04/Catwoman_poster.jpg/220px-Catwoman_poster.jpg"},
  {title: "Ghostbusters", description: "After the members of a team of scientists (Harold Ramis, Dan Aykroyd, Bill Murray) lose their cushy positions at a university in New York City, they decide to become \"ghostbusters\" to wage a high-tech battle with the supernatural for money. They stumble upon a gateway to another dimension, a doorway that will release evil upon the city. The Ghostbusters must now save New York from complete destruction", movie_length: "1:45", director: "Ivan Reitman", rating: "PG", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/I/91yW7SWyx9L.jpg"},
  {title: "Rain Man", description: "When car dealer Charlie Babbitt (Tom Cruise) learns that his estranged father has died, he returns home to Cincinnati, where he discovers that he has an autistic older brother named Raymond (Dustin Hoffman) and that his father's $3 million fortune is being left to the mental institution in which Raymond lives. Motivated by his father's money, Charlie checks Raymond out of the facility in order to return with him to Los Angeles. The brothers' cross-country trip ends up changing both their lives.", movie_length: "2:13", director: "Barry Levinson", rating: "R", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzVjNzI4NzYtMjE4NS00M2IzLWFkOWMtOTYwMWUzN2ZlNGVjL2ltYWdlL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTQxNzMzNDI@._V1_.jpg"},
  {title: "Gentlemen Prefer Blondes", description: "Lorelei Lee (Marilyn Monroe) is a beautiful showgirl engaged to be married to the wealthy Gus Esmond (Tommy Noonan), much to the disapproval of Gus' rich father, Esmond Sr., who thinks that Lorelei is just after his money. When Lorelei goes on a cruise accompanied only by her best friend, Dorothy Shaw (Jane Russell), Esmond Sr. hires Ernie Malone (Elliott Reid), a private detective, to follow her and report any questionable behavior that would disqualify her from the marriage.", movie_length: "1:31", director: "Howard Hawks", rating: "Not Rated ", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/S/pv-target-images/083d954b6596822ebe02373a2c4bf25897758ce235ba21a440d5c9d91ce11dfc._RI_V_TTW_.jpg"},
  {title: "Charlie and the Chocolate Factory", description: "Based on the beloved Roald Dahl tale, this comedic and fantastical film follows young Charlie Bucket (Freddie Highmore) and his Grandpa Joe (David Kelly) as they join a small group of contest winners who get to tour the magical and mysterious factory of eccentric candy maker Willy Wonka (Johnny Depp). Aided by his diminutive Oompa Loompa workers (Deep Roy), Wonka has a hidden motivation for the tour, one that he will reveal only after the children in the group show their true colors.", movie_length: "1:55", director: "Tim Burton", rating: "PG", user_id: 1, img_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjcxMjg1Njg2NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMjQ4NzMzMw@@._V1_.jpg"}
])
Review.create!([
  {rating: 4, comment: "If you haven't seen it, you are missing something very substantial in live action cinema. Iron Man 2008 is one of a kind movie. A perfect blend of comic book and contemporary reality. Jon Favreau has made this one with to kick start a new era. When I watched the 1st trailer in August 2007, I was blown away. I was counting months towards the release. Robert Downey Jr slides into Tony Stark's shoes with panache.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 2, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "A timeless classic in it’s own right, ‘Star Wars’ is the ultimate blockbuster film that launched a pop culture phenomenon and changed the cinema landscape forever. Part ‘Flash Gordon’, with Kurosawa and ‘The Wizard of Oz’ as other major influences, ‘Star Wars’ is an ambitious space opera that inspires audiences of all ages with it’s heroic story, loveable characters and the stakes our protagonists are up against.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 1, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 1, comment: "Did NOT like this movie. One of those films that get alot of hype..and does not deliver. Needless to say, Its a good thing Norman Reedus improved his acting skills in time for TWD!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 3, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 5, comment: "A truly awesome film. Tom Hardy made sure the film stayed closer to the comics and it really payed off, it was a pleasure to watch.\r\nIt had a lot of action, but not so much that it took over the plot.\r\nSome new and very interesting characters were introduced, and I enjoyed them very much. They were intriguing and you learned a lot about them quickly.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 4, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 4, comment: "I literally just saw this movie an hour ago and I thought it was pretty good! I have watched about the last half of the first Venom movie but I understood the plot. I got super excited when I found out I was going to see this movie! I loved Venoms temper and how he got upset and impatient quickly - it was really funny to me. I think the actor who portrayed Cletus Kasady (not carnage) did it in a perfect way. He was a psychopath and you guys made him seem crazy which is good. Tom Hardy did an excellent job, just like the first Venom. ", user_id: 1, movie_id: 4, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 1, comment: "Wheres the Venom? What we got was a sesame street version! Venom 1 was way better, plus it had a more believable story line! Why do we care about cletus or banshee??? Carnage is a villan and Venom is villan, play them that way until I believe in the change. Stopped watching when he went to the convenience store for reasons (choclate)", user_id: 1, movie_id: 4, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 3, comment: "A significant improvement over the previous entry\r\nBetter script.\r\nBetter story.\r\nInfinitely better special effects. \r\nAndy Serkis did a great job directing.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 4, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 4, comment: "This Movie was perfect to me. You are all probably asking why I love the original Star Wars that started in 1977 its because it introduced me to a whole new universe were there is space battles, light sabers, the force etc. Now the way George Lucas made this movie was amazing from special affects, perfect directing and a magnificent cast of characters this is how i fell in love with the franchise. I do have to say a couple of negatives to this movie is that when cgi was made and used in a lot of movies George went back on this movie and made it high tech which  i kinda like a little but he did a little to much high tech with the special edition versions of the originals and i kind of with we had the original versions of them on Disney + or on shelves. overall i still love this movie it has a place in my heart.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 1, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 2, comment: "I will excuse the cgi and the weird fight scenes for its time. But Christ Almighty, this movie was absolutely boring. I barely even remember anything that happened. I didn't even bother paying attention when it was near the end. I personally do love the story and I find it very intriguing, but the movie and how the story was told just kind of sucked.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 1, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 4, comment: "Sadly, the only reason this doesn't get five stars is because of the Special Editions.  The addition of heavy CGI into this movie kind of ruins it.  Now, even though I grew up watching the Special Editions, I would have definitely preferred to see the original.  All in all, though, this movie is great, fun, and at times, emotional.  And Darth Vader is easily one of the most recognizable film villains ever.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 1, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "This film is a masterpiece and heavily underrated. Some people say it's average, some people say it's just a rehash of Tarantino's work, but honestly it's its own thing and original as the story and characters involved. Acting is superb, funny and gets you in engaged in so many levels of emotions while watching fantastic action sequences and dialogue in many different areas. To be honest most of the film doesn't look like made up set-pieces but actual real places they shot in so I am intrigued as to the ratio of how practical it actually is. Back to the acting - this has to be the best if not in the top tier of Willem Dafoe's acting skill tree alone. He literally composes the story. I think one of the reasons this didn't perform well is due to the fact that it is way ahead of its time and in my opinion better than most of Tarantino's work if we are comparing quality.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 3, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 3, comment: "Worth a watch if you're a fan of action movies. But don't expect, as is mentioned in other reviews, better or as good as Tarantino or a masterpiece. It's a good fun movie with enough twists and turns to keep you entertained and occupied more than your average action flick. \r\n\r\nShockingly bad Irish accents from the two main characters though. Almost as though they were hired for how bad their accents are.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 3, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "This is an engagingly simple, good-hearted film, with just enough darkness around the edges to give contrast and relief to its glowingly benign view of human nature.\r\nBased on a novella by Stephen King, The Shawshank Redemption is a harrowing tale about the triumph of the human spirit. The story follows a banker named Andy Duphrane who's wrongfully convicted of killing his wife and her lover, and is sent to the Shawshank maximum security prison where he befriends another inmate named Red. Starring Tim Robbins, Morgan Freeman, John Sandler, and Clancy Brown, the film has an impressive cast that gives good performances. Additionally, screenwriter/director Frank Darabont does an excellent job at developing the characters and relationships; making the audience care about them and their plight. The set and costume designs too, are especially well-done; capturing the time-period and giving the prison a real, lived-in feel. Also, the score by Thomas Newman is emotionally evocative and has a soulfulness to it that heightens the material. The Shawshank Redemption is a remarkably compelling film with a powerful message.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 5, recommend: 1},
