  {rating: 4, comment: "Interesting concept, well executed overall. I'm sure many others have rich analyses of each detail that makes this film effective. I'll just provide a few of my nitpicks.\r\nI understand that the movie was building up to the escape, but I don't think it was worth dedicating the last 1/3 of the movie to. Not to mention that the transition into that portion with the ceiling hole seemed like a plot hole for someone being watched and broadcasted 24/7... I wish that time had been distributed to developing Truman and Sylvia's relationship and created some depth in their relationship beyond infatuation and sudden cutoff, although I'm sure that added to the intrigue and desire for the character. I also think an opportunity was missed in Marlon's dramatic line about betrayal and friendship. It wasn't really acknowledged afterwards. Perhaps this film was about the mystery and risk of breaking social norms, but don't we all know that? I wish it could have taken one step further.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 8, recommend: 1},
