  {rating: 5, comment: "Firstly I would like to say that all the hate surrounding this movie is completely uncalled for, the negative reviews are incredibly misleading, specifically the ones that just attack this movie without providing any constructive criticism, or giving any valid points. Anyway overall this was a good fast-paced action movie, not too stressful, with a nice plot that had its twists and turns, the frequent light-hearted comedic moments also made it very enjoyable to watch. The cast did an excellent job of portraying their characters and allowing the audience to connect/relate to them. Now I would not say that this is the best action movie I ever watched, but I would say that if you're looking for a light-hearted movie with some fighting/action scenes this one's for you.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 16, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 1, comment: "2019 had been a good year for movies. Although the reboots have been played out way too much. Charlies angels was a hit show back in the day and, the films that starred Cameron Diaz, Lucy Liu and, Drew Barrymore were also awful. Trying to resurrect this franchise was a mistake, not only on the production company but also Elizabeth banks as well. She blames the movies lack of success on men not attending the film because it’s starring women. That’s the biggest bunch of crybaby bs I’ve ever heard. I have no issue with women directing a movie at all. American psycho, Wonder Woman, captain marvel and, Wayne’s world are a few examples of movies that were directed by women and, they were all a huge success. Bottom line, the movie was mediocre at best and, you can tell it was directed by someone who doesn’t have very much experience. Stop with the reboots and, make something original!!!!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 16, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 3, comment: "I thought Charlie’s Angels was pretty good. Kristen did a great job kicking it off and never looked better. Ella is a fine actor with beauty to spare with her gorgeous length. Naomi is also a beauty with brains to boot. Elizabeth Banks does a good job as their Bosley and the chemistry is great amongst all of the women. The men in the movie are also very capable and talented and each one plays their role very well. The movie has good action, comedy and sensitivity. Nice car chases and the gadgets are used well and in one scene at the rock quarry with Naomi, well she tried to use the knockout lozenges and they worked, just not on the person intended. It was a tender moment with both Ella and Naomi crashing, Kristen made a great pillow. All three of the Angels had good humor but kicked some serious ass when needed. I will watch again.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 16, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "This movie remains possibly THE finest psychological drama I have ever seen, mixed with both outrage and subtle comedy. You can look at Jack Nicholson's face and know exactly what he is thinking. He has zero unconscious bias against anyone and just wants everyone to find a way to enjoy life. Not to mention how amazing that it debuted supporting actors such as Christopher Lloyd and Danny deVito.  This movie also made Nurse Ratched (sounds vaguely like wretched, or more like ratchet, a tool that clamps down but doesn't let go!) an icon for cruel treatment. Interesting that this movie was released just five years after Reagan signed the Lanterman-Petris-Short Act to end long term involuntary incarceration of mental patients.They just don't make movies like this anymore.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 17, recommend: 1},
