  {rating: 5, comment: "This is a brilliant movie that can be enjoyed by many generations. The physical comedy is amazing and perfectly timed. The running jokes about the poisonous human objects is always hilarious. As well as being a comedy that all ages can enjoy, this movie has heartfelt moments that feel deserved and therefore leave an impact on you and your appreciation of the movie. Sullies gradual move from being afraid of human children to eventually loving one named Boo is perfectly shown through the animation. The scene where he leaves Mike to save Boo choked me up when I first for this movie as a little boy to and still does a teenager. The score is amazing and the climax is beautifully done as it stops the amazing twist villain and ends the movie on a positive note. The upbeat score carries the scenes along effortlessly segmenting my view that this movie is in the top 3 best Pixar movies and that it will endure as an animated classic. Overall great movie.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 18, recommend: 1},
