  {rating: 5, comment: "I should say this movie is a masterpiece. I thought, of course, it's another brilliant movie because it has Meryl Streep in it who defines the standards of 'acting'. But I stand corrected. It's not just Meryl Streep who invents a new combination of smug and swag as an upper-classed fashionista boss but it's both her young P.As, Emily Blunt and Anne Hathway who have shown a lot of potential in elegantly sticking up to their roles and doing justice to it. Emily Blunt is simply fantastic and has mimicked the lifestyle of a hard-working underrated desperate personal assistant who awefully ends up to be a great disappointment to her boss against all her efforts. It's so subtle an acting style. Anne Hathway on the other hand has shown a character arc of transitioning from a regular girl to being swayed by a swirl of complex charcaters and personas that work with her and she has to put up with them in order to stay in the job. She goes an extra mile always and gets to decide what's best for her life. The other actors in the movie are well cast too. But Meryl Streep, Emily Blunt and Anne Hathway just stand out. If you're a connoisseur of fine arts and drama, you should definitely watch it for the over the top performances.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 19, recommend: 1},
