  {rating: 5, comment: "We watch every year on Groundhog Day, even invite people over and make a party of it. The special features on the disc are worth watching. Bill Murray saw all the extras freezing in the cold and decided they deserved some food. He cleaned out the local bakery of danishes and handed them out to the people himself. Legend. Harold Ramis and Bill have been close friends for a long time and apparently had a falling out during the filming of this movie. They didn't speak with each other again until Harold was on his death bed and Bill went to him ASAP to make amends. (Netflix series \"The Movies that Made Us\" - Ghostbusters episode)\r\nBoth Harold Ramis and Bill Murray are comedy legends and Chris Elliott's performance is awkwardly perfect. Tobolowsky has an equally unforgettable role. All of the actors in this film were flawless in execution and comedic timing.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 21, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "I love this film. Simply brilliant. What a great plot and cast. The concept is strange though, that Phil is caught in the same day over and over, however it works. Bill Murray was great as Phil and his comic presence, timing and characteristics were on show for us to enjoy. A wonderfully funny, yet poignant film. In 2020, with Covid, it seems we are all living the same day over and over but unlike this film, it isn't fun.  I've watched this film in lockdown and it was the very best tonic to ease anxiety.  A wonderfully presented film and a homage in one way to one similar made decades earlier called It's a Wonderful Life with the great Jimmy Stewart. Bill Murray at the very best in his career here. Please watch and enjoy.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 21, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Excellent movie. The theme is that it takes a 1000 years for some to science kindness and true love for others. There are some truly funny scenes-several involving piano playing. Bill Murray is awesome in the key title role. My wife and I got engaged on Ground Hog  Day years before the movie came out, but now we watch as part of our celebration of our engagement. The movie never gets olds. Highly recommend it.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 21, recommend: 1},
