  {rating: 5, comment: "When you want to steal $160 million in cash from huge casino in Las Vegas, you can either do it with force, or you can do it in a sneaky way. Danny Ocean (George Clooney) and his gang map out the casino and find a way to get down into the vault without anyone knowing what is going on until Rusty (Brad Pitt) calls the owner of the casino, Terry Benedict (Andy Garcia) to state the terms. A large reason for the heist was that Benedict was going out with Danny's sexy ex-wife Tess (Julia Roberts) and he wanted her back. The key to Danny and Linus (Matt Damon) getting into the vault was a device that Basher (Don Cheadle) stole, a bomb powerful enough to wipe out the power of Las Vegas. Not may people would find a movie about stealing money entertaining, but the way that this one was made certainly can catch people's eye. I really think that it is one of the best movie of the new decade. Final Verdict: One of The Best Heist Movies Ever.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 23, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Literally one of the best films ever made. Flawless imo I really can't think of one part to criticise. The futuristic world is super realistic and really seems plausible but the casting the comedy the story and best of all the Characters are superb. This film is never overplayed on TV and I think that's because even they realise it's a cult classic. The amount of thought and detail that went in to every single aspect of this film is epic. Milla is so so good she is really compelling to watch not only because she herself is flawless perfection but her acting is phenomenal she really is believable as a different being and she portrays the emotion better than the majority of a list actors. Bruce Willis is also great and even tho his character looks a bit like John Mclane he is so good you don't even see that and Gary Oldman is as always superb and so in to his character.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 25, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "\"5th Element\" remains one of our favorites, after years of movie watching - from the bad C-listers to AAA blockbusters. With lines that kids and adults can quote at each other, characters we still love to this day, and that vague science explanation that yadda-yaddas any concerns about \"how\" the 23rd century actually works. Even side-characters get played full of heart, despite Bruce Willis, Gary Oldman, Sir Ian Holm, and Chris Tucker chewing up the scenery to great effect. Brian James, Tom Lister, and Luke Perry, all go all-in with their roles despite a lack of extended screen time. And Milla Jovovich is ... \"perfect. Just...perfect.\"", user_id: 1, movie_id: 25, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 1, comment: "Made me cringe the first time i saw it, aged 23 or so. 30 years later I hate it even more. As a Sci Fi lover I'm affronted by the monodimensionality of the film. Made for 12 year old boys - except that I'd be reluctant to expose them to this level of banality. \r\nOne redeeming thing: the great Ian Holm.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 25, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Easily one of the best films of all time. Even after four more Pirates movies, this is still the superior entree in my opinion. I doubt there will ever be a more iconic role than Johnny Depp as Captain Jack Sparrow in this movie and he should've won that Oscar! \r\nThe plot, acting, CGI, character introductions, and cinematography in this film are far superior to any other film in the franchise. It has a great villain with Barbossa and perfectly balanced character developments along with entertaining parallels. This is one of those movies that's so perfect there is only one small plot hole in the third act regarding the Aztec gold. In all a truly PHENOMENAL movie with everything you want. 9.9/10 film!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 26, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Pirates of the Caribbean. Just WOW!!!! It was amazing, the plot was simple and beautiful. The characters were fully fleshed out and 3D with most of them getting a backstory. The visuals are stunning for 2003. CGI was just starting to look really good the and for its time, it is probably one of the best especially since skeletons are harder to make than metal for transformers or something like that. Now I have a personal connection with this movie so I might be a little biased about my review though. It got me through some difficult times.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 26, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 4, comment: "The second movie from Disney that is based on one of their amusement park attractions, however besides the name and curse this film has no more basis from that attraction. Captain Jack Sparrow and a blacksmith named Will Turner must save Elizabeth Swan from a cursed pirate crew. This is a well constructed movie with great writing, solid acting, wonderful soundtrack and a satisfying ending. Geoffrey Rush does a great job in the villain role and you can tell he really enjoyed playing the part. Johnny Depp also creates an iconic character in Captain Jack Sparrow. The score, written by Klaus Badelt, is also iconic and will be heard in the theme parks for decades. After the success of this movie they added Sparrow to the theme park attractions. A highly recommended movie, go check it out!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 26, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Thanks to Crichton's genius mind the world got to enter Jurassic Park. Literally a looking glass into the world of an extinct monster-sized species, and a new age of visual FX techniques that had only been touched upon by a few other ground breaking films before it. There is not a moment wasted in this film, combining adventure, wonder, comedy and horror in a perfectly balanced piece of immersive art. The pre-production itself was thoroughly planned out so there wasn't any room for Spielberg to experiment or deviate, but he held the reigns tightly and seen the picture through to it's best. Seeing this in the cinema as a kid was epic, and then going to Pizza Hut straight after and getting the Jurassic Park memorabilia will always be a part of my memories.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 27, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Jurassic Park has been, and will forever be, one of my favorite movies of all time. I have probably seen it 200 times in my 25 years of life, and hope to watch it 200 more times. The visual effects, writing, and pure attention to detail were astronomically amazing for a movie made in 1993. Even after watching it so many times, there has always been something new that I noticed or picked up on with each viewing. I also love that Jurassic Park is not overly filled with gore, and tastefully displays all of the dinosaur attacks in the movie. But even without all the gore, the suspense of the action coupled with the brilliantly scored soundtrack, keeps me on the edge of my seat even when I know exactly what is going to happen next. I adore the cast, love the story, and overall appreciate the full experience! Even with all of the little hiccups in the movie or the discrepancies in the plot- Jurassic Park is still a masterpiece in the end!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 27, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 4, comment: "Im 11, and I personallly enjoyed this film when I was little. me and my sis watched it when we were little, and mentioned that we want to b paleontologists and archeologists, so he suggested we watch this. Welp, at least it mentions turkeys, cuz i don't remember any real archeology being shown in this movie. obviously this isn't the best movie ever, it has its flaws, in fact, i personally think Godzilla vs Biollante(1989) was a better film, but otherwise, this was a great film, and i enjoyed it. Oh and Tyrannosaurus was awesome!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 27, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 3, comment: "Jurassic Park is a classically executed fun thriller movie. It delivers tension and fun simultaneously without conflict. It is a light hearted, well crafted movie with amazing special effects.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 27, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "This movie was just another take on the character that is Catwoman! did it have anything to do with the comic books? no. did it follow the original storyline? no. does it take place in gotham? no. is this movies amazing? YES! although it wasn’t like the comics, i believe that halle berry pulls this role off perfectly! though they spun it in a way that was different, it was creative and i think that they pulled it off wonderfully! halle berry’s commentary, and her performances as Patience and Catwoman amazes me! she pulled both off so well in the best way possible! OH AND THOSE CLOTHES!!!! UGHHH she nailed the look!!!!  this movie deserves way more than 3.3/10 stars and 9% on rotten tomatos. they just revamped her story and, in this case, it’s not a bad thing...", user_id: 1, movie_id: 28, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "I love catwoman so much and I love that a black female peas was casted, also I don’t know what these other critics was talking about but in my opinion this movie is one of the best versions I’ve seen, it keeps you interested and there is no dull moment. I’ve seen this movie way too many times to count and I absolutely love it one of my faves", user_id: 1, movie_id: 28, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 1, comment: "I’ll be honest I haven’t even watched the movie but just reading through peoples reviews? I can already tell watching this isn’t worth my time. My first gripe just reading the description though is, She magically got powers and is basically turned into a giant cat. Versus actually cat woman where she’s really agile and skilled with her whip, But nope instead she gets it from a cat. It makes no literal sense, And then on top of that they soiled a good actresses name by making her the star she wasn’t made for cat woman.  The fact that Warner bros approved This and spent so much money on it  I mean 100 million dollars??? People are out here homeless no money food or a roof over their head and we’re spending money on a movie this trash. Next time you make a cat woman  film do your research", user_id: 1, movie_id: 28, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 2, comment: "All I really like about this movie is the opening credits music. Other than that, it’s garbage. While it is interesting that they tried going for something different, they still probably could have been a little closer to the source material. And of course, there are plenty of things that are too silly or don’t make sense.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 28, recommend: 0},
  {rating: 5, comment: "On the best comedy films ever, it still holds up almost 40 years later.  The special effects look a little dated but that just makes the ghosts look that much scarier if you ask me!  The on screen chemistry between all the characters is clear from the get go, gags and puns are still funny and don't feel dated and even the 80's music fits well with the whole film (which isn't always the case with 80s films!).  Sigourney Weaver looks incredibly attractive in this film as well and I'm not a big fan of hers generally... Favourite scene has to be the ghost in the library which is very near the start, it sets the film up perfectly with the right amount of balance between scares and humour... And of course the giant Marshmallow Man but everybody says that!  I always laugh at Bill Murray's line \"yes it's true, that man has no dick\" - delivered so dry.", user_id: 1, movie_id: 29, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 5, comment: "Ghostbusters is the greatest Comedy/Fantasy of all time. The obvious greatest movie of all time in my opinion! With amazing and funny protagonists, an interesting and unique plot, and an adorable puffy villain, Ghostbusters exceeds all expectations. It easily wins the hearts of all who watch it, introducing creative paranormal equipment and instantly recognizable personalities. So many creative minds came together to create such a fantastic roller coaster of ideas, not even mentioning the coolest actors of the 80's! Adding the most advanced special effects and sets of the time, Ghostbusters always seems to go that extra mile. With literally millions of fans, I wouldn't be surprised to see at least a hundred people dressed in CWU-27p air suits (the Ghostbusters' original suits) on Halloween. I know I will be! A timeless classic that will always come through!", user_id: 1, movie_id: 29, recommend: 1},
  {rating: 1, comment: "It’s a terrible tragedy that they decided to make this movie this way, ppl have been hoping for 26 years (almost half a lifespan) to see the next one just for them to shovel this trash at them. My poor dad was so disappointed. I hear ppl say it was bad cuz of the woman and I get it would’ve been cool if they kept the original characters but honestly I think they would’ve screwed this up either way. It’s so sad that kids these day are just gonna get trash shoveled at them. The next one seems cool tho, let’s pray", user_id: 1, movie_id: 29, recommend: 0},
